Date: 0/0/1855
Source: Te Ika a Maui
Author: TAYLOR
Vol / Page: 412
Edition:
Quote: <i>Pihapiharau </i>(the lamprey), is almost eighteen inches long, of a silvery color; there is a saying, <i>`No Rangiriri te pihapiharau,' `The lamprey comes from the fountain of Rangiriri.</i>' The name of the fish is derived from its many gills. <i>Ibid.</i> 627 Fam. <i>Petromyzidae, (Pihapiharau,)</i> the Lamprey, which is found in most of the rivers to the south.
